  ${
    flimnei.1 $e |- X = U. J $.
    flimnei.2 $e |- Y = U. F $.
    $( A filter contains all of the neighborhoods of its limit points.
       (Contributed by Jeff Hankins, 4-Sep-2009.) $)
    flimnei $p |- ( ( ( J e. Top /\ F e. Fil /\ X = Y ) /\ A e. ( ( fLim1 ` J )
    ` F ) /\ N e. ( ( nei ` J ) ` { A } ) ) -> N e. F ) $=
      ( ctop wcel cfil wceq w3a cflim1 cfv csn cnei wa wss isfillim simplbda
      sseld 3impia ) CIJBKJEFLMZABCNOOJZDAPCQOOZJDBJUDUERUFBDUDUEAEJUFBSABCEFGH
      TUAUBUC $.
